Serra de Na Burguesa.label: Serra de Na Burguesa
Serra de Na Burguesa.description: Serra de Na Burguesa is a well-defined mountain on the island of Majorca, part of the Spanish autonomous community of the Balearic Islands. Wikipedia

Siebengebirge.label: Siebengebirge
Siebengebirge.description: The Siebengebirge is a German upland range to the East of the Rhine, southeast of Bonn, consisting of more than 40 hills. It is located in the municipalities of Bad Honnef and Königswinter. Wikipedia

Sierra de las Ánimas.label: Sierra de las Ánimas
Sierra de las Ánimas.description: Sierra de las Ánimas is a hill range which starts in Lavalleja Department of Uruguay and extends south into Maldonado Department where it includes one of the highest peaks of Uruguay, the top of Cerro ... Wikipedia

Southern Carpathians.label: Southern Carpathians
Southern Carpathians.description: The Southern Carpathians are a group of mountain ranges that divide central and southern Romania, on one side, and Serbia, on the other. Wikipedia

Türnitz Alps.label: Türnitz Alps
Türnitz Alps.description: The Türnitz Alps are a mountain range of the Northern Limestone Alps in southern Lower Austria and the adjacent state of Styria. They stretch from the Erlauf valley in the west to the valleys of the Traisen and Unrechttraisen in the east. Wikipedia

Stubai Alps.label: Stubai Alps
Stubai Alps.description: The Stubai Alps is a mountain range in the Central Eastern Alps of Europe. It is named after the Stubaital valley to its east. It is located southwest of Innsbruck, Austria, and several summits of the range form part of Austria's border with Italy. Wikipedia

Steinernes Meer.label: Steinernes Meer
Steinernes Meer.description: The Steinernes Meer is a high karst plateau in the Northern Limestone Alps. As one of the nine sub-ranges of the Berchtesgaden Alps the Steinernes Meer belongs partly to Bavaria and partly to Salzburg. Wikipedia

Styrian Prealps.label: Styrian Prealps
Styrian Prealps.description: The Styrian Prealps are a mountain range in the eastern part of the Alps. They are located in Austria and, marginally, in Slovenia and Hungary. Wikipedia

Tordrillo Mountains.label: Tordrillo Mountains
Tordrillo Mountains.description: The Tordrillo Mountains are a small mountain range in the Matanuska-Susitna and Kenai Peninsula Boroughs in the southcentral region of the U.S. state of Alaska. They lie approximately 75 miles west-northwest of Anchorage. Wikipedia

Tenasserim Hills.label: Tenasserim Hills
Tenasserim Hills.description: Tenasserim Hills or Tenasserim Range is the geographical name of a roughly 1,700 km long mountain chain, part of the Indo-Malayan mountain system in Southeast Asia. Wikipedia

United States Range.label: United States Range
United States Range.description: The United States Range is one of the most northern mountain ranges in the world and of the Arctic Cordillera and is surpassed only by the Challenger Mountains to the northwest. Wikipedia

Vanoise massif.label: Vanoise massif
Vanoise massif.description: The Vanoise massif is a mountain range in the Graian Alps in the western part of the Alps. Wikipedia

Sierra Carapé.label: Sierra Carapé
Sierra Carapé.description: Sierra Carapé or Sierra de Carapé is a hill range located in Maldonado Department, in southern Uruguay. The range crosses the Maldonado Department from west to east and enters the Rocha Department. Wikipedia

Sierra Madre Oriental.label: Sierra Madre Oriental
Sierra Madre Oriental.description: The Sierra Madre Oriental is a mountain range in northeastern Mexico. Wikipedia

Wrangell Mountains.label: Wrangell Mountains
Wrangell Mountains.description: The Wrangell Mountains are a high mountain range of eastern Alaska in the United States. Much of the range is included in Wrangell-Saint Elias National Park and Preserve. Wikipedia

Wetterstein.label: Wetterstein
Wetterstein.description: The Wetterstein, is a mountain range in the Northern Limestone Alps. It is a compact range between Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Mittenwald, Seefeld in Tirol and Ehrwald; partially in Bavaria, Germany and partially in Tyrol, Austria. Wikipedia

Ural Mountains.label: Ural Mountains
Ural Mountains.description: The Ural Mountains, or simply the Urals, are a mountain range that runs approximately from north to south through western Russia, from the coast of the Arctic Ocean to the Ural River and northwestern Kazakhstan. Wikipedia

Tian Shan.label: Tian Shan
Tian Shan.description: The Tian Shan, also spelled Tien Shan, is a large system of mountain ranges located in Central Asia. The highest peak in the Tian Shan is Victory Peak, 7,439 metres. Wikipedia

Sierra Salvada.label: Sierra Salvada
Sierra Salvada.description: Sierra Salvada is a mountain range situated to the northwest of Burgos, and it is also part of Alava and Orduña. The southern slope of this mountain range, whose rivers flow to the mediterranean sea, is included in the province of Burgos. Wikipedia

Vindhya Range.label: Vindhya Range
Vindhya Range.description: The Vindhya Range is a range of older rounded mountains and hills in the west-central Indian subcontinent, which geographically separates the Indian subcontinent into northern India and Southern India. Wikipedia

Şimleu Mountains.label: Şimleu Mountains
Şimleu Mountains.description: The Şimleu Mountains is a mountain range in Transylvania, Romania, which belongs to the Apuseni Mountains. Wikipedia

Sierra del Lacandón.label: Sierra del Lacandón
Sierra del Lacandón.description: The Sierra del Lacandón is a low karstic mountain range in Guatemala and Mexico. It is situated in the north-west of the department of El Petén and the south-east of Chiapas. Wikipedia

Shokanbetsudake Mountains.label: Shokanbetsudake Mountains
Shokanbetsudake Mountains.description: Shokanbetsudake Mountains are a group of volcanic mountains on the western coast of Hokkaidō. It is part of the Mashike Mountains, separated from the other part of the Mashike Mountains to the south, the Kabato Mountains by the Hamamasu River. Wikipedia

Sir Sandford Range.label: Sir Sandford Range
Sir Sandford Range.description: The Sir Sandford Range is a subrange of the Big Bend Ranges of the Selkirk Mountains of the Columbia Mountains in southeastern British Columbia, Canada, located between Gold and Palmer Creek just southwest of the Gold Arm of Kinbasket Lake. Wikipedia

Slovenian Prealps.label: Slovenian Prealps
Slovenian Prealps.description: The Slovenian Prealps are a group of mountain ranges in the eastern part of the Alps. They are located in Slovenia and, for a small part of their northernmost area, in Austria. Wikipedia

Seymour Range.label: Seymour Range
Seymour Range.description: The Seymour Range is a low and small mountain range comprising the mountains/hills between the valley of Cowichan Lake and that of the San Juan River on southern Vancouver Island, British Columbia, Canada. Wikipedia

Selter (hills).label: Selter
Selter (hills).description: The Selter is a ridge, up to 395 m above NN, in the Lower Saxon Hills in the districts of Hildesheim, Holzminden and Northeim in the German state of Lower Saxony. Wikipedia

Shawangunk Ridge.label: Shawangunk Ridge
Shawangunk Ridge.description: The Shawangunk Ridge, also known as the Shawangunk Mountains or The Gunks, is a ridge of bedrock in Ulster County, Sullivan County and Orange County in the state of New York, extending from the northernmost ... Wikipedia

Siskiyou Mountains.label: Siskiyou Mountains
Siskiyou Mountains.description: The Siskiyou Mountains are a coastal mountain range in the northern Klamath Mountains in northwestern California and southwestern Oregon in the United States. Wikipedia

South Mountain (Maryland and Pennsylvani.label: South Mountain
South Mountain (Maryland and Pennsylvani.description: South Mountain is the northern extension of the Blue Ridge Mountain range in Maryland and Pennsylvania. Wikipedia
South Mountain (Maryland and Pennsylvani.type: Mountain range in United States of America

Swan Range.label: Swan Range
Swan Range.description: The Swan Range is a mountain range in western Montana in the United States. Its peaks typically rise to around 8,000 to 9,000 feet. Wikipedia

Spearhead Range.label: Spearhead Range
Spearhead Range.description: The Spearhead Range is a short subrange of the Garibaldi Ranges of southwestern British Columbia, Canada, adjacent to the resort town of Whistler, British Columbia and ending at its northwestern apex ... Wikipedia

Supramonte.label: Supramonte
Supramonte.description: The Supramonte is an area of mountains and highlands located in central-eastern Sardinia, Italy. It lies northeast of the Gennargentu massif, spanning eastwards until it reaches the Tyrrenian See in the Gulf of Orosei. Wikipedia

Trinity Alps.label: Trinity Alps
Trinity Alps.description: The Trinity Alps are a mountain range in Siskiyou County and Trinity County, in Northern California. They are in the Klamath Mountains System, and located to the northwest of Redding. Wikipedia

Twin Range.label: Twin Range
Twin Range.description: The Twin Range is a mountain range within the White Mountains of New Hampshire. Wikipedia

Taconic Mountains.label: Taconic Mountains
Taconic Mountains.description: The Taconic Mountains or Taconic Range are a physiographic section of the larger New England province and part of the Appalachian Mountains, running along the eastern border of New York State and adjacent ... Wikipedia

Warm Springs, Nevada.label: Warm Springs
Warm Springs, Nevada.description: Warm Springs is an unincorporated community in the Tonopah Basin and Nye County, Nevada, near the mountain pass which divides the Kawich and Hot Creek ranges. Wikipedia

Whipple Mountains.label: Whipple Mountains
Whipple Mountains.description: The Whipple Mountains, 'Avii Kur'utat in the Mojave language, are located in eastern San Bernardino County, California. Wikipedia

Selenite Range.label: Selenite Range
Selenite Range.description: The Selenite Range is a mountain range in western Pershing County, Nevada. The range is a north–south trending feature approximately 27 miles long and 4 miles wide. Wikipedia

Stokes Range.label: Stokes Range
Stokes Range.description: The Stokes Range is a mountain range on Bathurst Island, Nunavut, Canada. The range is one of the northernmost ranges in the world and of the Arctic Cordillera. Its highest point is 412 m at Stokes Mountain. Wikipedia

The Palisades (Napa County).label: The Palisades
The Palisades (Napa County).description: The Palisades are a mountain range in Napa County, California. The Palisades are located in Robert Louis Stevenson State Park on the other side of California 29 as Mt. St. Helena. Wikipedia

Świętokrzyskie Mountains.label: Świętokrzyskie Mountains
Świętokrzyskie Mountains.description:
The Świętokrzyskie Mountains, or Holy Cross Mountains, are a mountain range in central Poland, in the vicinity of the city of Kielce.
The mountain range comprises several lesser ranges, the highest of which is Łysogóry. Wikipedia

Southern Rocky Mountains.label: Southern Rocky Mountains
Southern Rocky Mountains.description: The Southern Rocky Mountains are a major subregion of the Rocky Mountains of North America located in the southern portion of the U.S. state of Wyoming, the central and western portions of Colorado, ... Wikipedia

Sierra Vicuña Mackenna.label: Sierra Vicuña Mackenna
Sierra Vicuña Mackenna.description: The Cordillera Vicuña Mackenna is the highest section of the Chilean Coast Range located in northern Chile, west of Pampa del Tamarugal. Its peak reaches over 3000 meters. It runs north-south for approximately 170 km parallel to the Andes. Wikipedia

Sierra de Chinajá.label: Sierra de Chinajá
Sierra de Chinajá.description: The Sierra de Chinajá is a low karstic mountain range in Guatemala. It is situated in the north of the department of Alta Verapaz and covers an area of approximately 135 km². Its highest peak has an altitude of 838 m. Wikipedia

Western Carpathians.label: Western Carpathians
Western Carpathians.description: The Western Carpathians are a mountain range and geomorphological province that forms the western part of the Carpathian Mountains. Wikipedia

Selamiut Range.label: Selamiut Range
Selamiut Range.description: The Selamiut Range is a mountain range on the northernmost tip of Labrador, Canada. It is a subrange of the Torngat Mountains which in turn form part of the southern section of the Arctic Cordillera mountain system. Wikipedia

Wicklow Mountains.label: Wicklow Mountains
Wicklow Mountains.description: The Wicklow Mountains form the largest continuous upland area in Ireland. They occupy the whole centre of County Wicklow and stretch outside its borders into Counties Carlow, Wexford and Dublin. Wikipedia
Wicklow Mountains.type: Mountain range in Republic of Ireland

Sibola Range.label: Sibola Range
Sibola Range.description: The Sibola Range is a subrange of the Tahtsa Ranges, located north of Tahtsa Lake in northern British Columbia, Canada. Wikipedia

Sifton Ranges.label: Sifton Ranges
Sifton Ranges.description: The Sifton Ranges are a mountain range along the west side of the Rocky Mountain Trench in northern British Columbia, Canada. It has an area of 1820 km² and is a subrange of the Cassiar Mountains which in turn form part of the Interior Mountains. Wikipedia

Slamgeesh Range.label: Slamgeesh Range
Slamgeesh Range.description: The Slamgeesh Range is a small subrange of the Skeena Mountains of the Interior Mountains, located between the Skeena River and Slamgeesh River in northern British Columbia, Canada. Wikipedia

South Hills (Montana).label: South Hills
South Hills (Montana).description: The South Hills, is a term for a number of small foothills in various Montana communities, most notably those at el. 3,592 feet, south of Missoula, Montana in Missoula County, Montana. Wikipedia

Sourland Mountain.label: Sourland Mountain
Sourland Mountain.description: Sourland Mountain is a 17 miles long ridge in central New Jersey, extending from the Delaware River at Lambertville to the western end of Hillsborough Township near the community of Neshanic, through ... Wikipedia

Tangra Mountains.label: Tangra Mountains
Tangra Mountains.description: Tangra Mountains form the principal mountain range of Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands, Antarctica. The range had been nameless until 2001, when it was named after the Bulgar god Tangra. Wikipedia

Tatlatui Range.label: Tatlatui Range
Tatlatui Range.description: The Tatlatui Range is a large and very alpine mountain range on the east flank of the upper Skeena River in northern British Columbia, Canada. Wikipedia

Strata Range.label: Strata Range
Strata Range.description: The Strata Range is a small subrange of the Skeena Mountains of the Interior Mountains, located between the Bell-Irving River and Taylor River in northern British Columbia, Canada. Wikipedia

Telkwa Range.label: Telkwa Range
Telkwa Range.description: The Telkwa Range is a subrange of the Bulkley Ranges, located south of the junction of the Telkwa River and Bulkley River in northern British Columbia, Canada. Wikipedia

Three Buttes.label: Three Buttes
Three Buttes.description: The Three Buttes, el. 3,848 feet, are buttes or small, flat-topped hills northwest of Lodge Pole, Montana in Blaine County, Montana. Wikipedia

Transantarctic Mountains.label: Transantarctic Mountains
Transantarctic Mountains.description: The Transantarctic Mountains comprise a mountain range in Antarctica which extend, with some interruptions, across the continent from Cape Adare in northern Victoria Land to Coats Land. These mountains divide East Antarctica and West Antarctica. Wikipedia

Valkyr Range.label: Valkyr Range
Valkyr Range.description: The Valkyr Range is a subrange of the Selkirk Mountains of the Columbia Mountains in southeastern British Columbia, Canada, located on the east side of Lower Arrow Lake west of Nelson. Wikipedia

Waterman Mountains.label: Waterman Mountains
Waterman Mountains.description: The Waterman Mountains are a low mountainous landform in Pima County, United States. Notable among the tree species is the Elephant tree which species exhibits a contorted multi-furcate architecture; most of these froze in the cold winter of 2011. Wikipedia

Vancouver Island Ranges.label: Vancouver Island Ranges
Vancouver Island Ranges.description: The Vancouver Island Ranges, formerly called the Vancouver Island Mountains, is a mountain range extending along the length of Vancouver Island which has an area of 31,788 km². Wikipedia

Thiel Mountains.label: Thiel Mountains
Thiel Mountains.description: The Thiel Mountains are an isolated, mainly snow-capped mountain range in Antarctica which are 72 km long. Wikipedia

Whitesail Range.label: Whitesail Range
Whitesail Range.description: The Whitesail Range is a subrange of the Tahtsa Ranges, located north of Whitesail River in northern British Columbia, Canada. Wikipedia

Whatshan Range.label: Whatshan Range
Whatshan Range.description: The Whatshan Range is a subrange of the Monashee Mountains of the Columbia Mountains in southeastern British Columbia, Canada, located south of South Fosthall Creek. Wikipedia

Southern Limestone Alps.label: Southern Limestone Alps
Southern Limestone Alps.description: The Southern Limestone Alps are the ranges of the Eastern Alps south of the Central Eastern Alps mainly located in northern Italy and the adjacent lands of Austria and Slovenia. Wikipedia

White Mountains (New Hampshire).label: White Mountains
White Mountains (New Hampshire).description: The White Mountains are a mountain range covering about a quarter of the state of New Hampshire and a small portion of western Maine in the United States. Part of the northern Appalachian Mountains, they are the most rugged mountains in New England. Wikipedia
White Mountains (New Hampshire).type: Mountain range in United States of America

Upper Austrian Prealps.label: Upper Austrian Prealps
Upper Austrian Prealps.description: The Upper Austrian Prealps is a mountain range in Austria which, according to the Categorisation of the Eastern Alps, covers the region between the valley of the Traun in the west and the Enns valley in the east, from Steyr in the north. Wikipedia

Tibesti Mountains.label: Tibesti Mountains
Tibesti Mountains.description: The Tibesti Mountains are a mountain range in the central Sahara, primarily located in the extreme north of Chad, with a small extension into southern Libya. Wikipedia

Sudetes.label: Sudetes
Sudetes.description: The Sudetes is the scientific name of a mountain range in Central Europe also known in English – from their local designation in, respectively, German and Czech/Polish – as the Sudeten or Sudety mountains. Wikipedia

Zhiguli Mountains.label: Zhiguli Mountains
Zhiguli Mountains.description: The Zhiguli Mountains or simply Zhiguli, sometimes called The Zhiguli Heights - Жигулëвская возвышенность [Zhigulyovskaya vozvyshennost], are a range of wooded mountains located in Russia on the right bank of the Volga River, in the Samara bend. Wikipedia

White Carpathians.label: White Carpathians
White Carpathians.description:
The White Carpathians is the westernmost mountain range of the Carpathian Mountains.
They are part of the Slovak-Moravian Carpathians, stretching from the Váh river and the Little Carpathians in the ... Wikipedia

Tatra Mountains.label: Tatra Mountains
Tatra Mountains.description: The Tatra Mountains, Tatras or Tatra, are a mountain range that form a natural border between Slovakia and Poland. They are the highest mountain range in the Carpathian Mountains. Wikipedia

Zillertal Alps.label: Zillertal Alps
Zillertal Alps.description: The Zillertal Alps are a mountain range of the Central Eastern Alps on the border of Austria and Italy. The range is named after the Zillertal on its north. Wikipedia

Shadow Mountains.label: Shadow Mountains
Shadow Mountains.description: The Shadow Mountains are located in the Mojave Desert of eastern California in the United States. The mountains lie in a generally north-south direction south of the Kingston Range and east of the Avawatz Mountains and the Silurian Hills. Wikipedia
